## ğŸ”§ Auto-Cleanup Commands

Before committing, run these:

```bash
# Find documentation files that shouldn't be in root
find . -maxdepth 1 -name "*.md" ! -name "README.md" -type f

# Find temporary/scratch files
find . -name "TEMP_*.md" -o -name "SCRATCH_*.md" -o -name "*-OLD.md"

# Check for duplicate READMEs
find . -name "README*.md" | grep -v "^./README.md$"
```

**Action:** Move or delete these files before committing.

